<seg id="29">Mike Brown, 54, was still barefoot as he waited for permission to return to his trailer, which he thinks will be a total loss.</seg>
<seg id="30">The auto-salvage yard employee said he awoke to water all around him - even seeping into his bed.</seg>
<seg id="31">"My possessions were floating around," he said.</seg>
<seg id="32">I opened my door and swam out.</seg>
<seg id="33">The Red Cross deployed two relief trucks from Fort Worth to Austin to aid flood victims with cleanup.</seg>
<seg id="34">On a front lawn near Brown, landscaper Lee Dufrene was keeping watch over three small horses from a local ranch.</seg>
