<seg id="1">Insulin scientist JJR Macleod honoured by plaque in Aberdeen</seg>
<seg id="2">A plaque to remember the Nobel Prize-winning scientist who helped discover insulin is to be unveiled in Aberdeen.</seg>
<seg id="3">John James Rickard (JJR) Macleod was born in Perthshire in 1876 before moving to Aberdeen to live and work.</seg>
<seg id="4">The discovery paved the way for life-saving treatments for diabetics.</seg>
<seg id="5">A clinic at Foresterhill will be named in his honour, and a plaque will be unveiled to mark the JJR Macleod Centre for Diabetes, Endocrinology and Metabolism.</seg>
<seg id="6">The scientist was awarded the Nobel Prize in 1923, with Frederick Banting, for discovering insulin.</seg>
<seg id="7">Historian Prof Michael Bliss said: "The discovery of insulin was one of the most dramatic events in the history of medicine, and there was one of Aberdeen's sons at the heart of it."</seg>
<seg id="8">JJR Macleod died in 1935.</seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="e9a5dcab52a5fc4697e647bb7d414a1f" genre="news" origlang="xx">
<seg id="1">Car Salvage Firm Fined £40k Over Fireball Injury</seg>
<seg id="2">By Mike McCarthy, North of England Correspondent</seg>
<seg id="3">A car salvage company has been fined £40,000 plus £25,000 costs after a mechanic was engulfed in flames underneath a van.</seg>
<seg id="4">Lee Roberts, 33, was working in a vehicle inspection pit in Chorley, Lancashire, when he was set on fire.</seg>
<seg id="5">CCTV of the incident at Douglas Valley Breakers Ltd was played to a judge at Preston Crown Court.</seg>
<seg id="6">The company was prosecuted after a joint investigation by the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) and Lancashire Fire and Rescue Service discovered multiple health and safety failings.</seg>
<seg id="7">Mr Roberts said in a statement released by the HSE: "I still remember the noise of the petrol fumes igniting and a wave of blue flames engulfing the pit."</seg>
<seg id="8">""They put me into an induced coma to stop the pain and it was at least a couple of days later when I came round.</seg>
<seg id="9">When I woke up, I could feel the pain immediately.</seg>
<seg id="10">Even now, more than three years later, I still suffer flashbacks that cause me to wake in the middle of the night in a cold sweat.</seg>
<seg id="11">The court heard that workers at the salvage firm used electric drills to puncture fuel tanks and an extension lead in the pit may have caused ignition.</seg>
<seg id="12">The company had no fire alarms or detectors and the fire became so bad that the building was eventually condemned.</seg>
<seg id="13">Lancashire Fire and Rescue treated the blaze as a major incident.</seg>
<seg id="14">After the sentencing, HSE Inspector David Myrtle said Mr Roberts was lucky to be alive.</seg>
<seg id="15">He said: "The company had the right equipment to do the job properly but instead it allowed workers to stand in a pit surrounded by fuel vapours where just one spark could start a fire."</seg>
<seg id="16">Douglas Valley Breakers - which pleaded guilty to five charges of breaching safety regulation - said it has taken steps to make sure a similar incident doesn't happen in the future.</seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="ea1cc53fee8f2aecf28caa0e7f96f85f" genre="news" origlang="xx">
<seg id="1">Scottish Style Awards nominee The Finnieston are up for Most Stylish Bar</seg>
<seg id="2">With the nights drawing in and winter biting, The Finnieston is a welcome sanctuary from the cold, boasting an enviable cocktail menu and lively, eclectic clientele.</seg>
<seg id="3">They also do a great champers and fish and chips, and we're not the only ones that have noticed.</seg>
<seg id="4">The Finnieston already have a Dram Award for Best Cocktail Bar 2012 in the bag, have made it into the Michelin Guide and are now nominated for a Scottish Style Award for Most Stylish Bar 2013.</seg>
<seg id="5">Up against Glasgow's The Hill bar and three Edinburgh venues, the small team at The Finnieston hope their intimate West End bar will win out, but they're happy just to be nominated.</seg>
<seg id="6">We caught up with manager Dean Gannon to chat about naked martinis and all that jazz:</seg>
<seg id="7">So Dean, how does it feel to be nominated?</seg>
<seg id="8">It's fantastic to be nominated, it's not something we were expecting.</seg>
<seg id="9">It's been amazing.</seg>
