<seg id="12">This course is great, you put this in America and it would hold up to any of them over there.</seg>
<seg id="13">I think it's a great course, it's in great shape and the greens are really good but you have to be spot-on with your iron shots because there is a lot of undulation and today I controlled my distance really well and drove it really well.</seg>
<seg id="14">There are still two more days of golf left so I will come out tomorrow and try to do the same thing I did today.</seg>
<seg id="15">I don't tend to play defensively, I just play my game and I play pretty aggressively.</seg>
<seg id="16">McIlroy shared second place with 2012 Masters winner Bubba Watson and former Ryder Cup player Boo Weekley, the American duo recording rounds of 69 and 67 respectively.</seg>
<seg id="17">Six players are a shot behind on six under, defending champion Ian Poulter carding a 67 to join fellow Englishman Tommy Fleetwood, Spanish duo Sergio Garcia and Gonzalo Fernandez-Castano - winner of the BMW Masters on Sunday - Ernie Els and Graeme McDowell in fifth place.</seg>
<seg id="18">US Open champion Justin Rose and Open champion Phil Mickelson are among a seven-strong group on five under.</seg>
